09/03/2003
DUBROVNIK, Croatia -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia reiterated their plan to work together for NATO integration as well as their commitment to the international fight against terrorism.
The foreign ministers of the three countries -- Albania's Ilir Meta, Croatia's Tonino Picula and Macedonia's Ilinka Mitreva -- met in Dubrovnik on Friday (7 March), with US Ambassador to Croatia Lawrence Rossin in attendance.
They also worked to co-ordinate the final details of the draft Partnership Chapter that the three countries hope to seal with the United States this month.
Albania, Croatia and Macedonia are hoping for NATO admission in 2006.
(Dnevnik - 08/03/03;
A1 TV, ATA, HINA, BBC - 07/03/03)
